# Reusable Templates in GitLab

GitLab also supports **includes**:

```yaml id="1s5f47"
include:
  - template: Security/SAST.gitlab-ci.yml
```

This imports official GitLab templates for:

* SAST
* Dependency scanning
* Container scanning
* Auto DevOps

So “template” can also mean reusable predefined CI files.

